WEBVTT

00:02.785 --> 00:04.787
[ UTENSIL SCRAPING ]

00:12.664 --> 00:13.448
MORNING.

00:22.065 --> 00:24.372
AREN'T YOU
A LITTLE UNDERDRESSED?

00:24.459 --> 00:25.938
OH, HERE WE GO.

00:28.506 --> 00:30.160
IS THAT BETTER?
[ CHUCKLES ]
PERFECT.

00:33.511 --> 00:35.774
YOU KNOW, ONE OF THE PERKS
OF LIVING IN NEW YORK CITY

00:35.861 --> 00:37.559
IS THE CASUAL
EXHIBITIONISM.

00:37.646 --> 00:38.821
OH, ARE THE NEIGHBORS
COMPLAINING?

00:38.908 --> 00:40.257
NOT YET,
BUT THE SALE OF BINOCULARS

00:40.344 --> 00:41.954
HAS GONE UP SINCE YOU
STARTED COMING OVER.

00:42.042 --> 00:43.652
YEAH?
PERHAPS AFTER WE EAT,

00:43.739 --> 00:45.045
WE CAN RAISE
A FEW WINDOW SHADES.

00:45.132 --> 00:46.046
ALL RIGHT.

00:46.133 --> 00:47.090
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

00:47.177 --> 00:49.223
MOZZIE?

00:49.310 --> 00:50.963
OH, LATELY HE'S BEEN KNOCKING
IN IAMBIC PENTAMETER.

00:51.051 --> 00:52.400
OR NOT AT ALL.

00:52.487 --> 00:54.054
Peter: NEAL!PETER.

00:54.141 --> 00:55.316
REALLY GLAD
I DRESSED FOR COMPANY.
YEAH.

01:04.238 --> 01:06.675
YEAH?
LOCKED DOOR?

01:06.762 --> 01:08.677
THERE'S A LOT OF CRIME
IN THIS CITY.SO I'VE HEARD.

01:08.764 --> 01:10.635
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE THIS.

01:10.722 --> 01:14.509
THERE'S THIS CON MAN RUNNING
AROUND NEW YORK WHO --

01:14.596 --> 01:15.901
YOU MADE BREAKFAST.

01:15.988 --> 01:17.903
AM I NOT ALLOWED?

01:17.990 --> 01:19.557
BREAKFAST FOR TWO --

01:19.644 --> 01:21.777
ASSUMING THAT SECOND PLATE
ISN'T FOR ME.

01:21.864 --> 01:24.519
BRILLIANT. YOU WANT TO
IMPRESS ME WITH ANY MORE
OF YOUR DETECTIVE SKILLS?

01:24.606 --> 01:26.303
ALL RIGHT.

01:26.390 --> 01:28.566
[ SIGHS ]
WHY DID I ASK?

01:28.653 --> 01:33.528
OOH. TWO FRESH HEAD IMPRINTS
ON THE PILLOWS.

01:33.615 --> 01:36.052
CHAMPAGNE ICE BUCKET
AT THE FOOT OF THE BED.

01:36.139 --> 01:39.360
ROMANCE IS IN THE AIR.
[ HUMMING ]

01:39.447 --> 01:41.492
[ CLATTER ]THAT'S -- YEAH.

01:41.579 --> 01:43.146
OOH.

01:43.233 --> 01:46.932
AND THIS DETECTIVE HAS DECIDED
TO STOP DETECTING.

01:47.019 --> 01:48.804
LET'S SEE.

01:48.891 --> 01:50.414
DEPARTMENT ISSUE?

01:50.501 --> 01:53.113
UM, I'M S-- THOSE ARE MINE.
I'M SO...

01:53.200 --> 01:55.767
UH...

01:55.854 --> 01:57.595
NEAL'S TEACHING ME
HOW TO PICK THEM.

01:57.682 --> 01:59.423
IT'S OUR VERSION OF SUDOKU
IN THE AFTERNOON.

01:59.510 --> 02:00.685
YEAH.

02:00.772 --> 02:02.557
UH-HUH.
MORNING, SARA.
GOOD MORNING.

02:02.644 --> 02:03.819
AND BEFORE YOU ASK,

02:03.906 --> 02:06.126
I DO NOT HAVE A DRAWER HERE
OR A TOOTHBRUSH.

02:06.213 --> 02:07.823
DID I ASK?

02:07.910 --> 02:09.433
WE'RE IN THAT AWKWARD,
UNDEFINED STAGE

02:09.520 --> 02:11.043
WHERE, YES,
WE'VE BEEN ON A FEW DATES,

02:11.131 --> 02:12.349
BUT, REALLY,
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

02:12.436 --> 02:14.177
WHAT DOESIT ALL MEAN?

02:14.264 --> 02:15.961
IT MEANS WE'RE TAKING THINGS
ONE DAY AT A TIME.

02:16.048 --> 02:17.659
THAT'S WHAT I SAID.MORE OR LESS.

02:17.746 --> 02:18.790
MOSTLY MORE.

02:18.877 --> 02:20.401
[ CELL PHONE CHIMES ]

02:22.054 --> 02:24.274
AH.
OUR NEXT CASE AWAITS.

02:24.361 --> 02:26.668
MM.
WELL,
YOU TWO HAVE FUN.

02:26.755 --> 02:28.191
NO, NO.OH, NO, NO, NO, NO!
YOU DON'T HAVE TO --

02:28.278 --> 02:29.671
IT'S...BYE.

02:29.758 --> 02:30.846
BYE.

02:30.933 --> 02:32.239
BYE, SARA!
YEAH.

02:34.545 --> 02:35.459
YOU SHOULD GET DRESSED.

02:35.546 --> 02:36.895
MM-HMM.

02:36.982 --> 02:38.897
I'M GONNA EAT.
YEAH, PLEASE.

02:38.984 --> 02:40.247
HURRY UP!
YOU CAN HAVE BOTH.

02:44.729 --> 02:47.645
THIS GUY'S A SKILLED FORGER,
SAFE CRACKER,

02:47.732 --> 02:49.734
LOTS OF PANACHE,
AND HE'S ONLY 20 YEARS OLD.

02:49.821 --> 02:51.823
THINK WE MIGHT BE LOOKING
AT THE NEXT NEAL CAFFREY.

02:51.910 --> 02:53.260
MM-HMM.

02:53.347 --> 02:55.653
HE'S A HACKER.
I DON'T HACK.

02:55.740 --> 02:57.089
YOU'RE RIGHT.

02:57.177 --> 02:59.004
A NEAL CAFFREY
FOR THE NEW MILLENNIA, THEN.

02:59.091 --> 03:01.833
WHEN I WAS 20,
I DIDN'T GET CAUGHT.

03:05.097 --> 03:07.665
WE TRACED HIM
TO THIS APARTMENT.

03:07.752 --> 03:10.538
IS HE IN THERE?
THERE'S
MOVEMENT INSIDE.

03:10.625 --> 03:12.409
Peter:
YEAH, I SEE IT.

03:12.496 --> 03:15.020
PLEASE TELL ME I GET TO
BREAK DOWN THE DOOR.

03:15.107 --> 03:16.544
WHY,
WHEN YOU ASK SO NICELY...

03:23.333 --> 03:24.552
FBI!
HANDS IN THE --

03:26.641 --> 03:29.209
OH-HO! CUTE.

03:29.296 --> 03:30.558
YOU WANT ME
TO CUFF IT?

03:30.645 --> 03:33.474
YEAH, WE SHOULD HOLD IT
FOR QUESTIONING.

03:33.561 --> 03:35.345
WHY ARE YOU SMILING?[ CHUCKLES ]

03:35.432 --> 03:36.738
HE'S CLEVER.

03:36.825 --> 03:38.870
IT CASTS A SHADOW
ON THE DOOR

03:38.957 --> 03:40.568
AND DOESN'T MOVE
IN A FIXED PATTERN.

03:40.655 --> 03:42.526
HE REALIZED WE WERE
SITTING ON HIM AND BOLTED.

03:42.613 --> 03:43.919
LOOKS LIKE THAT.

03:44.006 --> 03:45.921
THEY DIDN'T HAVE ROBOT VACUUMS
IN YOUR DAY?

03:46.008 --> 03:47.792
NO, THEY DIDN'T.

03:47.879 --> 03:49.403
MM.
LOOK AROUND.

03:49.490 --> 03:52.232
HE'S GOT TO HAVE
AN ESCAPE ROUTE SOMEWHERE.

03:55.757 --> 03:57.846
YOU'RE ENJOYING THIS.

03:57.933 --> 04:00.501
I LOVE TRACKING
THE SMART ONES.

04:00.588 --> 04:02.851
NOW THAT YOU'RE ON MY SIDE,
I MISS THE CHALLENGE.

04:02.938 --> 04:04.200
OH, COME ON,
ALL HE'S DONE

04:04.287 --> 04:06.158
ARE A FEW MILDLY IMPRESSIVE
FORGERIES,

04:06.246 --> 04:08.030
ALLEGEDLY CRACKED
A SAFE,

04:08.117 --> 04:09.945
AND STUCK A VASE
ON A ROOMBA.

04:10.032 --> 04:12.208
WHAT?
NOTHING.

04:12.295 --> 04:13.514
Diana: BOSS,
YOU NEED TO SEE THIS.

04:22.784 --> 04:24.176
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

04:24.264 --> 04:26.570
COMPLETELY RANDOM ARRANGEMENT
OF PHOTOGRAPHS?

04:26.657 --> 04:28.920
ALL RIGHT...
MAYBE HE ISGOOD.

04:48.723 --> 04:50.986
[ RHYTHMIC KNOCK ON DOOR ]

04:51.073 --> 04:52.901
ENTREZ,MOZ.

04:52.988 --> 04:55.295
AH.

04:55.382 --> 04:57.732
I'VE COME
TO STEAL YOUR SOUL.

04:57.819 --> 04:59.168
OR AT LEAST PARTOF IT.

04:59.255 --> 05:01.170
YOU KNOW, I'VE ALWAYS FOUND
THAT SUPERSTITION

05:01.257 --> 05:02.911
ANNOYINGLY INCONSISTENT.

05:02.998 --> 05:04.869
YEAH, I GOT TO
GET TO THE OFFICE.

05:04.956 --> 05:07.132
UH, THIS WILL ONLY
TAKE A MOMENT.

05:07.219 --> 05:10.179
NOW, WHILE I AM DISAPPOINTED
WE HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE

05:10.266 --> 05:13.051
TO RECOVER PETER'S PARTIAL LIST
OF OUR TREASURES,

05:13.138 --> 05:14.923
THERE IS
A SILVER LINING.

05:15.010 --> 05:17.752
GIVES US TIME TO PERFECTLY
PREPARE FOR OUR ESCAPE.

05:17.839 --> 05:20.058
MM.
STARTING WITH PASSPORTS?

05:20.145 --> 05:24.541
HOW LONG DO OUR ALIASES
USUALLY LAST?

05:24.628 --> 05:26.978
PETER CAUGHT ON TO "NICK HALDEN"
IN TWO MONTHS.

05:27.065 --> 05:29.198
"STEVE" SURVIVED
FOR A YEAR.
SAY "GOUDA."

05:29.285 --> 05:30.765
NO.[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

05:30.852 --> 05:33.333
IMAGINE NOT HAVING TO
LOOK OVER OUR SHOULDERS,

05:33.420 --> 05:35.378
NOT HAVING TO MEMORIZE
A NEW DATE OF BIRTH

05:35.465 --> 05:36.858
EVERY FEW MONTHS.

05:36.945 --> 05:38.642
I KNOW WHERE YOU'RE GOING
WITH THIS, MOZ.

05:38.729 --> 05:40.862
A PERMANENT IDENTITY
THAT THE FBI CAN NEVER CRACK

05:40.949 --> 05:42.951
REQUIRES THE BIRTH CERTIFICATE
FOR A DEAD INFANT.

05:43.038 --> 05:44.213
I'M NOT DOING IT.

05:44.300 --> 05:46.346
SAY "BRIE DE MEAUX."

05:46.433 --> 05:49.349
WHAT IF THERE WAS A WAY TO DO IT
THAT WASN'T SO...

05:49.436 --> 05:50.698
HORRIFYING?

05:50.785 --> 05:52.003
HOW'S IT WORK?

05:52.090 --> 05:54.223
YOU'LL BE STEPPING
INTO SOMEONE ELSE'S SHOES,

05:54.310 --> 05:57.444
EVEN THOUGH THEY OR THEIR SHOES
NEVER EXISTED.

05:57.531 --> 05:58.967
RIDDLES, MOZ?

06:00.838 --> 06:03.406
NEAL...TRUST ME.

06:03.493 --> 06:05.800
IF THERE IS A WAY...

06:05.887 --> 06:07.018
I'M IN.

06:07.105 --> 06:08.585
EXCELLENT.

06:08.672 --> 06:10.065
I'LL SET IT UP.

06:16.898 --> 06:18.769
OUR SUSPECT'S NAME
IS SCOTT RIVERS,

06:18.856 --> 06:20.815
AND HE'S BEEN
ON A CRIMINAL ROAD TRIP.

06:20.902 --> 06:23.339
SO FAR, WE'VE BEEN ABLE
TO LINK SEVEN OF THE ITEMS

06:23.426 --> 06:25.123
IN THE PHOTOS
TO RECENT CRIMES.

06:25.210 --> 06:26.995
WE HAVE A WARRANT
FOR HIS ARREST,

06:27.082 --> 06:29.650
BUT OUR GUY
IS ALWAYS IN DISGUISES.

06:29.737 --> 06:31.216
HE WON'T BE EASY
TO TRACK DOWN.

06:31.303 --> 06:32.914
HEY, HOW COME
YOU NEVER USED DISGUISES?

06:33.001 --> 06:34.785
THE RIGHT SMILE WORKS
JUST AS WELL,

06:34.872 --> 06:37.397
AND YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY THAT
YOUR MUSTACHE IS ON STRAIGHT.

06:37.484 --> 06:39.399
OH, THIS KID DID
THE HARTFORD MANSION JOB?

06:39.486 --> 06:40.574
[ WHISTLES ]

06:40.661 --> 06:42.097
OOH.
OOH.

06:42.184 --> 06:44.447
HE STEALS ITEMS OF INCREDIBLE
EXCESS FROM THE WEALTHY --

06:44.534 --> 06:46.406
HALF-A-MILLION-DOLLAR
SUNGLASSES,

06:46.493 --> 06:48.277
A SOLID-GOLD
TOILET-BRUSH HOLDER --

06:48.364 --> 06:49.539
YOU GET THE IDEA.

06:49.626 --> 06:51.149
AND EVERY CRIME
HE COMMITS,

06:51.236 --> 06:53.543
HE LEAVES
THIS SIGNATURE BEHIND.

06:53.630 --> 06:56.067
DOES HE ACTUALLY
LEAVE A DONATION?

06:56.154 --> 06:57.199
IN THE VICTIMS' NAMES,

06:57.286 --> 06:58.766
TO A DIFFERENT CHARITY
EACH TIME.

06:58.853 --> 07:01.159
SO, ROBIN HOODIE HERE
ROBS FROM THE RICH

07:01.246 --> 07:02.857
AND GIVES SOME
TO THE POOR.

07:02.944 --> 07:04.598
ROBIN HOODIE?I LIKE IT.

07:04.685 --> 07:06.643
NO, YOU DON'T.
DON'T CALL HIM THAT, PLEASE.

07:06.730 --> 07:07.775
WELL, YOUCALLED HIM THAT.

07:07.862 --> 07:09.080
IT WAS A BAD JOKE.

07:09.167 --> 07:10.125
WHAT CAN YOU TELL US
ABOUT HIM?

07:10.212 --> 07:11.779
HE'S A KID.

07:11.866 --> 07:13.650
I MEAN, HE LIKES SHINY THINGS,
AND HE STEALS THEM.

07:14.956 --> 07:17.698
HE NEVER HAD MUCH MONEY,

07:17.785 --> 07:20.048
BUT HE WAS AROUND PEOPLE
WHO DID, AND HE RESENTS THEM.

07:20.135 --> 07:21.615
HE'S GOT MORALS.

07:21.702 --> 07:24.269
THESE DONATION CARDS ARE A WAY
TO JUSTIFY HIS THEFTS.

07:24.356 --> 07:26.184
HE'S TELLING THEM HOW
THEY SHOULDSPEND THEIR MONEY.

07:26.271 --> 07:27.925
AND HE'S COCKY.

07:28.012 --> 07:29.492
ALMOST GETTING CAUGHT
WON'T STOP HIM.

07:29.579 --> 07:30.711
WILL HE GET BOLDER?

07:30.798 --> 07:32.756
THAT'S WHAT IDID.

07:32.843 --> 07:36.717
OKAY. NEAL AND I
WILL DIG INTO THE DONATIONS

07:36.804 --> 07:39.415
AND THE EVIDENCE
FROM THE SAFE HOUSE.

07:39.502 --> 07:42.723
JONES, DIANA, FIND OUT
WHERE THE REST OF THOSE
STOLEN ITEMS CAME FROM.

07:42.810 --> 07:45.856
LET'S TRY AND FIGURE OUT
WHERE THIS GUY'S GONNA HIT NEXT.

07:45.943 --> 07:49.338
HI, HONEY!
HEY!

07:49.425 --> 07:52.123
I, UH, SAW YOU GOT A HIGH SCORE
ON "ANGRY BIRDS" TODAY.

07:53.516 --> 07:55.475
SHE KNOWS YOU'RE HERE.OH, I'M NOT JUDGING.

07:55.562 --> 07:56.954
SOMEBODY HAS TO STAND UP
TO THOSE GREEN PIGS.

07:57.041 --> 07:59.217
I'M GLAD YOU'RE WORKING
FROM HOME TONIGHT.

07:59.304 --> 08:01.002
SO, WHAT'S THE CASE?

08:01.089 --> 08:03.483
YOUNG CON MAN STEALING
FROM NEW YORK'S WEALTHY.

08:03.570 --> 08:05.006
OH, A YOUNG NEAL?

08:05.093 --> 08:06.486
TOUCHY SUBJECT?

08:06.573 --> 08:07.748
APPARENTLY.
IT'S NOT.

08:07.835 --> 08:10.228
THIS IS IT.

08:10.315 --> 08:11.752
THIS IS
THE BANK ACCOUNT

08:11.839 --> 08:13.231
ROBIN HOODIE USED
TO MAKE THE DONATIONS.

08:13.318 --> 08:14.711
ROBIN HOODIE?
I LIKE IT.

08:14.798 --> 08:17.018
HE MADE A DONATION
YESTERDAY,

08:17.105 --> 08:18.933
BUT IT DOESN'T LINK UP
TO A ROBBERY.

08:19.020 --> 08:21.805
MAYBE SOMETHING
THAT HE HASN'T STOLEN YET?

08:21.892 --> 08:24.025
NO, HE NEEDS TO MAKE
THE DONATION TO GET THE CARD.

08:24.112 --> 08:25.983
THE THEFT HAS TO
COME AFTER THAT.

08:26.070 --> 08:28.290
WHICH MEANS IT COULD BE
HAPPENING ANY MINUTE.

08:29.987 --> 08:31.989
WELL, HIS DONATIONS DEFINITELY
HAVE A SENSE OF HUMOR.

08:32.076 --> 08:33.643
HE STOLE A HALF-MILLION-DOLLAR
BOTTLE OF SCOTCH,

08:33.730 --> 08:34.862
THEN DONATED
TO THE BETTY FORD CLINIC.

08:34.949 --> 08:36.211
MM-HMM.

08:36.298 --> 08:39.475
THIS ONE'S TO
AN ORGAN-DONATION CHARITY.

08:39.562 --> 08:41.608
MAYBE HE'S STEALING
A RARE CHURCH ORGAN.

08:41.695 --> 08:43.958
PLAY ON WORDS.

08:44.045 --> 08:45.916
ORGAN DONATION --
MAKES YOU THINK OF?

08:46.003 --> 08:48.266
DRIVER'S LICENSE.
ORGAN DONOR.

08:48.353 --> 08:50.747
HE'S GONNA ROB
THE DMV?

08:50.834 --> 08:52.836
THERE'S NO REAL PATTERN
TO THE THINGS HE STEALS.

08:52.923 --> 08:54.969
IT'S EVERYTHING FROM A
DIAMOND-COVERED CELL PHONE TO --

08:55.056 --> 08:56.361
WHAT ABOUT
A MOTORCYCLE?

08:56.448 --> 08:59.277
HOSPITALS CALL THEM
"DONORCYCLES."

08:59.364 --> 09:00.888
IT'S WORTH A SHOT.

09:00.975 --> 09:02.498
LET'S FIND OUT
WHO OWNS

09:02.585 --> 09:04.805
THE MOST EXPENSIVE MOTORCYCLE
IN NEW YORK.

09:06.807 --> 09:08.548
LOCK IT UP.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.724
MR. STEWART,
WE SUSPECT

09:10.811 --> 09:12.726
YOU'RE ABOUT TO BE
THE TARGET OF THEFT.

09:12.813 --> 09:13.988
THAT SUCKS.

09:14.075 --> 09:15.555
WE'RE SERIOUS.

09:15.642 --> 09:17.600
YOU RECENTLY BOUGHT
A HIGH-END MOTORCYCLE?

09:17.687 --> 09:19.515
NO.YOU DIDN'T?

09:19.602 --> 09:22.126
I BOUGHT A CONFEDERATE
FIGHTER, OKAY?

09:22.213 --> 09:25.216
CALLING IT A MOTORCYCLE IS LIKE
CALLING THE QUEEN OF ENGLAND

09:25.303 --> 09:28.480
A RICH OLD LADY
WITH A FUNNY ACCENT.

09:28.568 --> 09:30.395
BUT IT'S STILL
A MOTORCYCLE.

09:30.482 --> 09:33.181
DUDE,
THIS IS SO MUCH MORE.

09:38.099 --> 09:40.492
HAVE YOU EVER HAD 100 GRAND
BETWEEN YOUR LEGS?

09:40.580 --> 09:43.017
ACTUALLY, YES,
I HAVE.
DON'T. DON'T.

09:43.104 --> 09:45.106
WE'D LIKE TO SET UP
A COMMAND POST HERE
TO CATCH THE THIEF.

09:45.193 --> 09:46.716
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

09:46.803 --> 09:48.631
MY CONFEDERATE PARTY'S
IN FOUR HOURS --

09:48.718 --> 09:50.720
FOR THIS CONFEDERATE.

09:50.807 --> 09:52.766
YOU REALLY LIKE SAYING
"CONFEDERATE," DON'T YOU?

09:52.853 --> 09:55.420
CONFEDERATE.WHO KNOWS
ABOUT THE PARTY?

09:55.507 --> 09:57.988
EVERYBODY.IT'S THE PERFECT OPPORTUNITY
FOR THE THEFT.

09:58.075 --> 09:59.337
MY SECURITY ROCKS.

09:59.424 --> 10:01.122
NO ONE'S STEALING
ANYTHING FROM HERE.

10:01.209 --> 10:02.427
YOU WANT TO MAKE
A BET ON THAT?

10:02.514 --> 10:04.691
HELL, YEAH.

10:04.778 --> 10:07.389
I BET YOU I CAN STEAL
SOMETHING WORTH...

10:07.476 --> 10:09.696
10 GRAND
IN THE NEXT TWO MINUTES.

10:09.783 --> 10:11.175
IF I DO, YOU LET US
COME TO THE PARTY.

10:11.262 --> 10:13.613
SURE. WHY NOT?

10:17.442 --> 10:19.096
IS THIS A JOKE?

10:19.183 --> 10:20.794
YOU'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.
YOU ONLY HAVE...

10:20.881 --> 10:23.448
A MINUTE LEFT.
I KNOW.

10:23.535 --> 10:24.972
HOW MUCH WOULD YOU SAY
THIS IS WORTH?

10:25.059 --> 10:26.538
10 GRAND?OH, AT LEAST.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.715
I GET IT.

10:28.802 --> 10:30.194
YOU DIDN'T SAY
I HAVE TO GIVE IT BACK.

10:31.239 --> 10:33.502
GIVE IT BACK.

10:33.589 --> 10:35.635
FINE.
YOU CAN SET UP HERE.

10:35.722 --> 10:38.289
I GOT THE FBI
AT MY BECK AND CALL?

10:38.376 --> 10:39.813
EVERYBODY'S GONNA
LOVE THIS.

10:39.900 --> 10:42.119
NO, THE WHOLE POINT
OF A COVERT STING

10:42.206 --> 10:43.599
IS TO NOT
TELL PEOPLE.

10:43.686 --> 10:45.253
NO ONE CAN KNOW
WE'RE HERE.

10:45.340 --> 10:46.733
[ CHUCKLES ]
IN THAT SUIT?

10:46.820 --> 10:48.212
RIGHT.

10:50.432 --> 10:51.955
I'LL BE IN THE SURVEILLANCE VAN
FOR THIS ONE.

10:52.042 --> 10:53.174
CAN I COME
WITH YOU?
NO.

10:53.261 --> 10:54.610
PLEASE?
NO.

10:56.786 --> 10:59.136
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

10:59.223 --> 11:01.791
UNDERCOVERS
ARE IN POSITION.

11:01.878 --> 11:03.706
AGENT DAVIES IS
AT THE SOUTH ENTRANCE.

11:03.793 --> 11:05.229
AGENT WESTLEY IS...

11:05.316 --> 11:07.231
GETTING CHAD A BEER.

11:12.846 --> 11:14.195
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:14.282 --> 11:15.805
CHAD TOLD ME
TO GET HIM A DRINK.

11:15.892 --> 11:17.372
I'M UNDERCOVER
AS HIS BUDDY.

11:17.459 --> 11:19.548
DID HE ALSO TELL YOU
TO DOUBLE FIST IT?

11:19.635 --> 11:22.116
NO. HE SAID THAT YOU
NEED TO LOOSEN UP?

11:22.203 --> 11:23.944
COME ON.

11:25.772 --> 11:28.122
HI, THERE.

11:28.209 --> 11:30.037
CHAD SAYS
YOU'RE AN FBI AGENT.

11:30.124 --> 11:32.604
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

11:32.692 --> 11:35.869
HE'S SCARED OF GUNS.
YEAH.

11:35.956 --> 11:38.785
OKAY, IT'S TIME TO PUT
THE FEAR OF GOD IN HIM.

11:38.872 --> 11:41.004
YEAH.

11:42.136 --> 11:43.659
HEY, CHAD.

11:45.443 --> 11:48.229
I'M NOT SURE HOW LONG
OUR COVER'S GONNA LAST, PETER.

11:48.316 --> 11:50.361
YOU NEED TO MAKE POSITIVE I.D.
ON OUR YOUNG THIEF

11:50.448 --> 11:51.406
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

11:51.493 --> 11:52.929
STAY ALERT.

11:53.016 --> 11:55.236
WHO KNOWS WHAT DISGUISE
HE'LL BE WEARING THIS TIME?

11:55.323 --> 11:59.501
I'LL LOOK
FOR THE CROOKED MUSTACHE.

11:59.588 --> 12:01.938
HEY, IF YOU'RE HUNTING
ROBIN HOODIE,

12:02.025 --> 12:03.810
DOES THAT MAKE YOU
THE SHERIFF OF NOTTINGHAM?

12:03.897 --> 12:06.029
OH, I'M NOT THE SHERIFF
OF NOTTINGHAM.

12:06.116 --> 12:07.378
AM I?

12:13.776 --> 12:16.126
CHAD SAYS YOU'RE
INTO BODY SHOTS.

12:16.213 --> 12:18.128
I AM.

12:18.215 --> 12:19.739
PETER: Stay on target,
Caffrey.

12:19.826 --> 12:21.131
BUT NOT TONIGHT.

12:21.218 --> 12:25.309
DESIGNATED DRIVER.
SORRY.

12:28.399 --> 12:30.619
I GOT EYES
ON A POTENTIAL SCOTT.

12:30.706 --> 12:32.577
Why do you think
it's him?

12:32.664 --> 12:34.841
HE'S WEARING
A SUIT HOODIE.

12:34.928 --> 12:36.799
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT THAT IS.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.061
All right,
confirm it's him,

12:38.148 --> 12:39.541
then Jones will move in
for the arrest.

12:46.287 --> 12:48.724
YOU ARE IN SO FAR
OVER YOUR HEAD,

12:48.811 --> 12:50.508
AND YOU HAVE NO IDEA,
DO YOU?

12:50.595 --> 12:52.772
YOU SAY SOMETHING?

12:52.859 --> 12:55.209
NO, I WAS JUST
ADMIRING THIS BIKE.

12:55.296 --> 12:56.993
SURE DOES
LOOK EXPENSIVE.

12:57.080 --> 12:59.735
120 GRAND.
DAMN.

12:59.822 --> 13:03.086
HAVE WE MET?
UH, I'VE SEEN YOU SOMEWHERE.

13:03.173 --> 13:05.001
STAND BY IN CASE
CAFFREY'S BEEN MADE.

13:05.088 --> 13:06.437
EVERYBODY
READY TO MOVE.

13:06.524 --> 13:08.091
MAYBE CHAD'S PARTY
LAST WEEK?

13:08.178 --> 13:09.484
WASN'T THERE.

13:09.571 --> 13:10.790
OH, MAN,
YOU MISSED OUT.

13:10.877 --> 13:12.748
THEY HAD MERMAIDS.

13:12.835 --> 13:16.665
I MEAN, LITERALLY, GIRLS
WEARING TAILS AND NOTHING ELSE.

13:16.752 --> 13:19.146
AND ALL HE HAS FOR THIS PARTY
IS A MOTORCYCLE?

13:19.233 --> 13:20.800
POOR GUY.

13:20.887 --> 13:22.366
OH, COME ON, MAN.

13:22.453 --> 13:27.110
IT'S A CARBON FIBER AND TITANIUM
CHASSIS, 1966 CC ENGINE.

13:27.197 --> 13:30.897
TOP SPEED OF 260 KILOMETERS
PER HOUR...

13:30.984 --> 13:33.421
AND NOT REMOTELY
STREET LEGAL.

13:33.508 --> 13:35.336
IT'S A WORK OF ART
ON TWO WHEELS.

13:35.423 --> 13:37.947
HI. I'M SHANNON.

13:38.034 --> 13:40.210
HEY.

13:40.297 --> 13:43.257
EXCUSE ME.

13:45.172 --> 13:47.087
IT'S HIM.PETER: You're sure?

13:47.174 --> 13:48.784
BEAUTIFUL GIRL
JUST GAVE HIM HER NAME,

13:48.871 --> 13:50.264
AND HE DIDN'T
GIVE ONE BACK.

13:50.351 --> 13:52.744
THERE'S SOMETHING
SUSPICIOUS ABOUT HER.

13:52.832 --> 13:55.660
THE FACT THAT SHE SEEMED
MORE INTERESTED IN HIM THAN YOU?

13:55.747 --> 13:57.749
NOT THAT.

13:57.837 --> 13:58.838
NOT ENTIRELYTHAT.

14:00.927 --> 14:03.277
SHE JUST PUT SOMETHING
IN HIS DRINK.

14:03.364 --> 14:05.105
EXCUSE ME!WHOA!
WHAT THE HELL?!

14:05.192 --> 14:06.410
SORRY.

14:06.497 --> 14:07.934
JONES!Woman: OH, MY GOD!

14:08.021 --> 14:09.805
FBI!EVERYBODY DOWN!

14:09.892 --> 14:11.546
LOCK DOWN THE EXITS.
NOBODY GETS OUT.

14:11.633 --> 14:13.417
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

14:17.857 --> 14:20.816
[ ENGINE REVS, TIRES SCREECH ]

14:42.925 --> 14:44.840
YOU NEED TO
TELL US EVERYTHING.

14:44.927 --> 14:46.581
WE'RE GONNA FIND
WHO HIRED YOU EVENTUALLY.

14:46.668 --> 14:48.931
BUT IF YOU HELP US NOW,
WE CAN MAKE A DEAL.

14:49.018 --> 14:51.499
WHAT DO WE KNOW
ABOUT HER?

14:51.586 --> 14:56.547
SHE'S BEEN A SUSPECT
IN SOME HEISTS AND ROBBERIES.

14:56.634 --> 14:58.723
ATTEMPTED MURDER'S
A NEW ONE, THOUGH.

14:58.810 --> 15:00.073
SO I'M GUESSING
IT WASN'T SPLENDA

15:00.160 --> 15:01.465
THAT SHE SPRINKLED
IN SCOTT'S DRINK.

15:01.552 --> 15:03.206
POTASSIUM CYANIDE.

15:03.293 --> 15:04.338
HE WOULD HAVE BEEN DEAD
IN MINUTES.

15:05.730 --> 15:07.645
I DIDN'T BUY THE RING.

15:07.732 --> 15:09.604
IT'S A LITTLE GOTHIC
FOR MY TASTE,

15:09.691 --> 15:11.127
BUT I NEVER
REFUSE JEWELRY.

15:11.214 --> 15:12.433
NOW, LET ME GUESS.

15:12.520 --> 15:14.000
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
THERE WAS POISON INSIDE.

15:14.087 --> 15:15.653
OOPS.

15:15.740 --> 15:17.351
HOW'S SHE
CONNECTED TO HIM?

15:17.438 --> 15:20.267
THIS MIGHT HAVE
SOMETHING TO DO WITH IT.

15:20.354 --> 15:22.486
FOUND IT
IN HER PURSE.

15:22.573 --> 15:26.360
ONE OF THE PEOPLE SCOTT ROBBED
HAD A SECURITY CAMERA.

15:26.447 --> 15:27.970
HE DIDN'T SEE IT.

15:28.057 --> 15:29.798
THAT'S ANOTHER REASON
I DON'T LIKE DISGUISES.

15:29.885 --> 15:31.278
TOO EASY
TO GET COMFORTABLE?

15:31.365 --> 15:33.758
MM-HMM. IT ALSO EXPLAINS
HOW OUR GIRL FOUND HIM.

15:33.845 --> 15:36.109
SO, I GUESS THEY TOOK MEASURES
INTO THEIR OWN HANDS.

15:36.196 --> 15:37.806
YEAH.

15:37.893 --> 15:40.591
WE'LL RUN
THAT PHOTO THROUGH,

15:40.678 --> 15:43.203
SEE WHICH ITEM HE STOLE
WHILE WEARING THIS WIG.

15:47.120 --> 15:49.122
WHAT DO YOU
THINK OF HIM?

15:49.209 --> 15:53.691
HE'S A KID HAVING
THE TIME OF HIS LIFE.

15:53.778 --> 15:55.476
HE'S IMPULSIVE,
ARROGANT,

15:55.563 --> 15:57.652
AND HAS NO IDEA HOW DEEPLY
IN OVER HIS HEAD HE IS.

15:57.739 --> 15:59.132
OKAY, FINE.

15:59.219 --> 16:02.265
HE BEARS A CURSORY
RESEMBLANCE TO ME.

16:02.352 --> 16:04.267
THINK CAN WE BRING HIM BACK
FROM THE DARK SIDE?

16:04.354 --> 16:06.182
IT'S HARD TO DO.

16:06.269 --> 16:07.879
I WONDER WHAT
WOULD'VE HAPPENED

16:07.967 --> 16:09.533
IF I'D HAVE
CAUGHT YOU EARLIER.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.535
IT WOULDN'T HAVE MADE
A DIFFERENCE, PETER.

16:12.667 --> 16:14.974
THE CON IS A RUSH.

16:15.061 --> 16:17.498
IT'S AN ADDICTION.

16:17.585 --> 16:19.891
AND YOU NEED TO HIT ROCK BOTTOM
BEFORE YOU CAN CHANGE.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.545
WHEN DID YOU
HIT BOTTOM?

16:21.632 --> 16:22.982
I NEVER SAID I DID.

16:24.809 --> 16:26.898
Neal: NICE BUSTIER.
FOR YOU OR CHRISTIE?

16:26.986 --> 16:28.422
THIS IS ONE
OF THREE ITEMS

16:28.509 --> 16:30.554
ROBIN HOODIE STOLE
WHILE WEARING THAT WIG.

16:30.641 --> 16:32.426
ARE WE REALLY GONNA
KEEP CALLING HIM THAT?

16:32.513 --> 16:33.644
SURE.
IT'S NO "JAMES BONDS."

16:33.731 --> 16:34.863
NO, IT'S NOT.

16:34.950 --> 16:36.473
AND THESE DIAMONDS
ARE FROM A HEIST

16:36.560 --> 16:38.301
OUR LADY KILLER
WAS A SUSPECT IN.

16:38.388 --> 16:41.087
SO, SCOTT THOUGHT HE STOLE
AN EXPENSIVE PIECE OF JEWELRY.

16:41.174 --> 16:43.176
INSTEAD, HE STOLE
EVIDENCE OF A CRIME.

16:43.263 --> 16:45.178
KILL SCOTT, AND THEY
ELIMINATE ANY EVIDENCE

16:45.265 --> 16:46.614
THAT LEADS BACK TO THEM.

16:46.701 --> 16:48.877
THE OFFICE IN THIS PICTURE
HAS AN UNOBSTRUCTED VIEW

16:48.964 --> 16:50.487
OF MIDTOWN
FROM AN UPPER FLOOR.

16:50.574 --> 16:52.576
LET'S SEE IF WE CAN FIGURE OUT
ELEVATION AND ANGLES

16:52.663 --> 16:53.969
TO SEE WHERE IT IS.

16:54.056 --> 16:56.015
DONE.LOOK AT YOU.

16:56.102 --> 16:58.234
THE OFFICE BELONGS
TO THOMAS CARLISLE.

16:58.321 --> 17:00.019
HE WAS SUSPECTED
OF MASTERMINDING THE HEIST.

17:00.106 --> 17:01.455
WHAT AN INCREDIBLE
COINCIDENCE.

17:01.542 --> 17:02.934
I'VE HEARD
OF MR. CARLISLE.

17:03.022 --> 17:04.936
HE HAS BEEN A PERSON OF INTEREST
MORE THAN A FEW TIMES.

17:05.024 --> 17:06.677
LET'S GO TALK TO HIM.

17:06.764 --> 17:09.506
NEAL, SEE IF YOU CAN GET
ANY LEADS ON SCOTT.

17:11.378 --> 17:13.945
OH, YOU'RE GONNA LOVE THIS.
THE STREET IS ABUZZ.

17:14.033 --> 17:15.947
SOMEONE IS LOOKING
FOR YOU.

17:16.035 --> 17:18.428
NO NAME.
HE'S A KID.

17:18.515 --> 17:22.041
WORD IS HE TALKS THE TALK,
SO TO SPEAK THE SPEAK.

17:22.128 --> 17:23.520
DID YOU ENJOY
THAT SENTENCE?
YES, I DID.

17:23.607 --> 17:26.088
SO HE'S TRYING
TO FIND ME.

17:26.175 --> 17:28.438
MAKES YOUR JOB EASIER.I WANT YOU TO GET
IN TOUCH WITH HIM.

17:28.525 --> 17:31.311
I WILL. BUT FIRST, WE HAVE
A LITTLE IDENTITY CRISIS.

17:33.269 --> 17:35.097
[ BOTH SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

17:35.184 --> 17:36.185
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:36.272 --> 17:37.534
THIS IS
MY ASSOCIATE --

17:37.621 --> 17:39.188
YOU ARE ABOUT
TO BE REBORN.

17:39.275 --> 17:40.711
NAMES ARE NOT NECESSARY.

17:40.798 --> 17:42.670
MOZZIE SAYS YOU CAN CREATE
PERMANENT IDENTITIES

17:42.757 --> 17:44.150
WITHOUT THE BABY
BIRTH CERTIFICATES.

17:44.237 --> 17:45.847
IDENTITY FARMING.

17:45.934 --> 17:47.849
I'VE HEARD OF IT,
BUT ONLY AS A THEORY.

17:47.936 --> 17:49.677
HOW'D YOU
PULL THAT OFF?

17:49.764 --> 17:52.941
YEARS AGO, I BEGAN FILING FOR
A NUMBER OF BIRTH CERTIFICATES.

17:53.028 --> 17:54.551
BACK THEN,
IT WAS MUCH EASIER.

17:54.638 --> 17:56.162
THE WORLD
WAS MORE TRUSTING.

17:56.249 --> 17:58.686
WE LIVE IN
CYNICAL TIMES, ALEC.

17:58.773 --> 18:00.209
OH, YEAH,
THIS IS TRUE.

18:00.296 --> 18:03.299
I TREATED THESE IDENTITIES
AS IF THEY WERE REAL.

18:03.386 --> 18:06.172
AS THEY GREW UP,
I GAVE THEM BANK ACCOUNTS,

18:06.259 --> 18:09.436
LIBRARY CARDS,
TAX RETURNS.

18:09.523 --> 18:11.133
YOU CREATED
PAPER TRAILS.

18:11.220 --> 18:13.353
I CREATED LIVES,

18:13.440 --> 18:15.746
ONE OF WHICH
YOU WILL NOW STEP INTO

18:15.833 --> 18:17.313
AS IF YOU HAD
LIVED IT ALL ALONG.

18:19.576 --> 18:21.274
YOU WILL BE VICTOR.

18:21.361 --> 18:23.493
I DON'T KNOW
IF I'M A VICTOR. I --YES, YOU ARE.

18:23.580 --> 18:27.628
STRONG-WILLED,
SO STUBBORN GROWING UP.

18:27.715 --> 18:29.151
AND HE'S YOUR AGE.

18:29.238 --> 18:31.762
VICTOR MOREAU.

18:31.849 --> 18:33.677
DID YOU PLAN THIS?

18:33.764 --> 18:35.897
NO. DESTINY?

18:37.028 --> 18:38.552
GOOD-BYE, VICTOR.

18:41.642 --> 18:43.948
NOW YOU.

18:44.035 --> 18:45.211
YOU ARE NOW BOB.

18:46.777 --> 18:48.083
I NEVER LIKED YOU.

18:53.001 --> 18:55.438
I LIKE YOU, BOB.

18:55.525 --> 19:00.704
Diana: A JAPANESE SCULPTURE,
AN ITALIAN HARP,

19:00.791 --> 19:02.619
AND FRAMED
SPANISH DOUBLOONS.

19:02.706 --> 19:04.926
CAN'T REALLY SETTLE
ON A THEME, CAN HE?

19:05.013 --> 19:08.147
I THINK THE POINT IS THAT
EVERYTHING IS REALLY EXPENSIVE.

19:08.234 --> 19:10.061
NO MATTER
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

19:10.149 --> 19:12.847
AGENTS!

19:12.934 --> 19:16.416
I HOPE THIS ISN'T ABOUT
THAT DIAMOND HEIST A YEAR AGO,

19:16.503 --> 19:19.636
BECAUSE YOU GUYS HAVE
HASSLED ME PLENTY ALREADY,

19:19.723 --> 19:21.595
AND YOU HAVEN'T
FOUND ANYTHING.

19:21.682 --> 19:23.597
IT ISN'T.
THIS IS A FRIENDLY VISIT.

19:23.684 --> 19:26.991
GREAT.
LET'S HAVE A DRINK.

19:27.078 --> 19:29.559
WHAT'S YOUR PLEASURE,
UM...

19:29.646 --> 19:31.735
FBI AGENTS BURKE
AND BERRIGAN.

19:31.822 --> 19:33.172
Diana:
AND, NO, THANKS.

19:33.259 --> 19:36.218
THE 7X3000
REINFORCED TITANIUM.

19:36.305 --> 19:38.438
IT'S A BEAUTY...
AND BRAND-NEW.

19:38.525 --> 19:39.787
IT IS.

19:39.874 --> 19:42.833
IT'S THE MOST EXPENSIVE
MODEL THEY GOT.

19:42.920 --> 19:44.487
ANY REASON
YOU NEED A NEW SAFE?

19:44.574 --> 19:46.750
AHH.

19:46.837 --> 19:48.361
A MAN IN MY POSITION,

19:48.448 --> 19:50.319
PEOPLE TRY TO STEAL FROM ME
ALL THE TIME.

19:50.406 --> 19:51.842
THESE ATTEMPTS
GET REPORTED?

19:51.929 --> 19:53.235
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

19:53.322 --> 19:55.106
I DO?
YEAH.

19:55.194 --> 19:56.978
INSTEAD OF WORKING
THEIR WAY UP LIKE I DID,

19:57.065 --> 19:58.371
THEY TRY
TO TAKE SHORTCUTS.

19:58.458 --> 20:00.068
WANT TO TAKE
WHAT ISN'T THEIRS.

20:00.155 --> 20:01.809
ANYONE STOLEN
FROM YOU RECENTLY?

20:01.896 --> 20:03.245
IF THEY HAD,
THEY'D REGRET IT.

20:03.332 --> 20:04.290
HOW'S THAT?

20:04.377 --> 20:05.769
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

20:05.856 --> 20:08.250
'CAUSE YOU GUYS WOULD
ARREST THEM, OF COURSE.

20:08.337 --> 20:09.947
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:10.034 --> 20:12.123
OF COURSE.
THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE.

20:12.211 --> 20:14.169
DO YOU RECOGNIZE
THIS KID?

20:15.692 --> 20:18.217
I DON'T.
WHAT DID HE DO?

20:18.304 --> 20:20.001
HE TOOK A SHORTCUT --

20:20.088 --> 20:21.959
TOOK SOME THINGS
THAT WEREN'T HIS.

20:22.046 --> 20:24.745
HE'S BEEN ROBBING WEALTHY PEOPLE
IN THE AREA WHO COLLECT...

20:24.832 --> 20:26.268
ITEMS OF EXTRAVAGANCE.

20:26.355 --> 20:28.096
YOU CERTAINLY
FIT THE BILL.

20:28.183 --> 20:29.837
One of
your guys called.

20:29.924 --> 20:31.491
They know
where he's at.

20:34.233 --> 20:37.061
I GOTTA GO.
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE YOU NEED?

20:37.148 --> 20:41.152
CALL ME IF YOU SEE HIM
OR HEAR ANYTHING, WILL YOU?

20:41.240 --> 20:42.893
OF COURSE.

20:44.460 --> 20:45.505
LOVELY GUY.

20:45.592 --> 20:47.289
HE'S A PEACH.

20:47.376 --> 20:49.030
THE KIND OF MAN
WHO'D BE STUPID ENOUGH

20:49.117 --> 20:51.685
TO PUT STOLEN DIAMONDS
ON A BUSTIER.

20:51.772 --> 20:54.818
SO, THAT REALLY WAS
NEAL CAFFREY AT THE PARTY?

20:54.905 --> 20:56.516
IN THE INFAMOUS FLESH.

20:56.603 --> 20:58.169
[ CHUCKLES ]
I KNEW I RECOGNIZED HIM.

20:58.257 --> 21:00.868
SO,
YOU WORK FOR HIM?

21:00.955 --> 21:01.999
WORK WITHHIM.

21:02.086 --> 21:04.785
KIND OF LIKE A MENTOR.

21:04.872 --> 21:06.569
HE LEARNED EVERYTHING
FROM ME.

21:06.656 --> 21:08.615
SO, THEN, HOW COME
I'VE NEVER HEARD OF YOU?

21:08.702 --> 21:09.964
EXACTLY.

21:14.403 --> 21:15.491
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]OH.

21:15.578 --> 21:19.103
AH.
AH, THE MAN HIMSELF.

21:19.190 --> 21:20.931
YOU'RE BEING FOLLOWED.

21:21.018 --> 21:23.412
LOOK TO THE SOUTHWEST.

21:23.499 --> 21:25.414
YOUR OTHERSOUTHWEST,
MOZ.

21:27.024 --> 21:29.766
YOU KNOW, IN MY DEFENSE,
I ALWAYS CARRY A COMPASS.

21:29.853 --> 21:32.247
It's Carlisle.
You need to stall him.

21:32.334 --> 21:33.509
YOU EVER PULL
A SCROOGE McDUCK?

21:33.596 --> 21:35.163
W-WHAT'S THAT?

21:35.250 --> 21:37.208
STEP ONE --
HACK AN ATM.

21:37.296 --> 21:38.601
HOW ARE YOU GONNA GET PAST
THE ENCRYPTED LOCKOUT?

21:38.688 --> 21:42.126
OH, I EXPLOIT AN UNPATCHED
SECURITY FLAW IN THEIR FIRMWARE,

21:42.213 --> 21:43.998
WHICH GIVES ME
ADMIN ACCESS.

21:44.085 --> 21:45.347
NICE.

21:45.434 --> 21:48.350
THEN I PUT IT INTO A TEST LOOP,
AND VOILÃ .

21:48.437 --> 21:49.699
WHAT'S STEP TWO?

21:49.786 --> 21:51.005
NOW YOU RUN.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.528
Man: HEY, THAT ATM'S
SPITTING OUT MONEY!

21:52.615 --> 21:54.400
Woman:
HEY, CHECK IT OUT!

21:54.487 --> 21:56.445
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]HOLY CRAP,
THERE'S MONEY EVERYWHERE!

21:58.578 --> 22:01.363
SLOW DOWN.

22:01.450 --> 22:02.886
IT'S NEW YORK CITY.

22:02.973 --> 22:04.888
ONCE YOU GET SOME DISTANCE,
IT'S BETTER TO BLEND IN.

22:04.975 --> 22:07.021
SORRY. I DON'T THINK
CLEARLY WHEN PEOPLE
ARE TRYING TO KILL ME.

22:07.108 --> 22:09.415
NEVER SAY YOU'RE SORRY
UNLESS YOU'RE RUNNING A CON.

22:09.502 --> 22:11.547
WHATEVER.
IS THE FBI HERE?

22:11.634 --> 22:13.375
NO.

22:13.462 --> 22:15.856
BUT YOU SHOULD
TURN YOURSELF IN.

22:15.943 --> 22:17.466
YOU'RE NEAL CAFFREY.

22:17.553 --> 22:20.295
ARE YOU REALLY TELLING ME
THERE ISN'T ANOTHER WAY?

22:24.255 --> 22:25.605
GET IN HERE.

22:25.692 --> 22:27.433
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:35.092 --> 22:37.399
YOU BROUGHT A WANTED FUGITIVE
INTO YOUR HOME.

22:37.486 --> 22:38.966
IT WOULDN'T BE
THE FIRST TIME.NOT HELPING.

22:39.053 --> 22:40.054
AND PETER DOESN'T
KNOW HE'S HERE.

22:40.141 --> 22:41.360
WHAT IS SHE DOING HERE?

22:41.447 --> 22:42.361
I WAS HERE TO SURPRISE NEAL
WITH DINNER.

22:42.448 --> 22:43.623
SURPRISE.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.538
Neal: PETER DOESN'T KNOW
HE'S HERE YET.

22:45.625 --> 22:47.148
I'M STILL DECIDING WHAT
I'M GONNA DO WITH HIM.

22:47.235 --> 22:48.671
HE'S ONE OF OUR OWN,
NEAL.

22:48.758 --> 22:51.500
WE HAVE TO HELP HIM.
IT'S PART OF THE CODE.

22:51.587 --> 22:53.937
BESIDES,
I KIND OF LIKE HIM.

22:54.024 --> 22:55.069
HE REMINDS ME
OF A YOUNG...

22:55.156 --> 22:57.811
DON'T SAY IT.
...ME.

22:59.116 --> 23:00.117
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

23:00.204 --> 23:01.336
WHY ARE YOU ASKING HER?

23:01.423 --> 23:02.772
I THINK
YOU SHOULD HELP HIM.

23:02.859 --> 23:04.295
BRILLIANT WOMAN.

23:04.383 --> 23:06.254
I THINK YOU SHOULD HELP HIM
GET OUT OF TROUBLE

23:06.341 --> 23:07.951
AND THEN CONVINCE HIM
TO TURN HIMSELF IN.

23:08.038 --> 23:09.649
OKAY, THAT'S ABSURD.

23:09.736 --> 23:11.825
GIVE HIM A CHANCE
TO LIVE A LIFE,

23:11.912 --> 23:13.348
MAKE HIS MARK
ON THE WORLD.

23:13.435 --> 23:15.394
THIS IS YOURCHANCE TO SHOW HIM
THERE'S ANOTHER WAY.

23:15.481 --> 23:16.917
WELL, I'M NOT EXACTLY
A ROLE MODEL.

23:17.004 --> 23:18.353
YOU'RE PROBABLY
THE CLOSEST THING HE HAS.

23:23.314 --> 23:24.838
[ SIGHS ]

23:26.535 --> 23:28.189
I NEED YOUR HELP.

23:29.712 --> 23:32.976
I NEVER STOLE FROM ANYBODY
WHO DIDN'T DESERVE IT.

23:33.063 --> 23:35.414
NEVER HURT ANYONE.

23:35.501 --> 23:39.983
I FIGURED YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE,
WOULD UNDERSTAND THAT.

23:45.467 --> 23:49.340
ALL RIGHT, LET'S FOCUS
ON THE FIRST PART.

23:49.428 --> 23:52.996
WE NEED TO FIGURE OUT HOW
TO GET CARLISLE OFF YOUR BACK.

23:53.083 --> 23:54.998
TAKE A SEAT, KID.

24:05.139 --> 24:06.619
Scott: SO,
YOU AND NEAL ARE DATING.

24:06.706 --> 24:07.968
Mozzie: HEY.Sara: UH, IT'S COMPLICATED.

24:08.055 --> 24:09.535
HEY.

24:09.622 --> 24:12.799
WHILE SCOTT'S OUT THERE
HITTING ON YOUR LADY FRIEND,

24:12.886 --> 24:15.366
TAKE A LOOK AT BOB.

24:18.587 --> 24:19.675
MM.

24:19.762 --> 24:21.285
IT'S TRULY
AMAZING WORK.

24:21.372 --> 24:22.591
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:22.678 --> 24:23.984
NO ONE'S EVER GONNA
FIND US, NEAL.

24:24.071 --> 24:25.812
WE CAN BE TAKING OFF
TO PARADISE

24:25.899 --> 24:27.901
AS SOON AS WE GET AHOLD
OF THAT LIST.

24:27.988 --> 24:29.424
UNLESS WE GET ARRESTED
FOR HARBORING A FUGITIVE FIRST.

24:29.511 --> 24:30.469
[ SCOFFS ]

24:30.556 --> 24:32.122
OR SCOTT
PINS THIS ON US

24:32.209 --> 24:33.559
SO HE CAN LIVE
TO STEAL ANOTHER DAY.

24:33.646 --> 24:35.996
OH, HE ISN'T
GONNA DO THAT.

24:36.083 --> 24:37.911
I SENSE GOOD IN HIM.

24:37.998 --> 24:39.478
DO YOU, QUI-GON JINN?

24:39.565 --> 24:42.045
WELL, CHAOTICGOOD,
ANYWAY.

24:42.132 --> 24:44.178
NEAL, HE'S US.

24:44.265 --> 24:46.702
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

24:46.789 --> 24:47.660
THIS IS PETER.

24:47.747 --> 24:48.617
OH.

24:50.401 --> 24:51.707
HEY, PETER.

24:51.794 --> 24:54.710
ANY WORD ON THE STREET
WHERE SCOTT MIGHT BE?

24:54.797 --> 24:57.626
NO, THE STREETS DON'T SEEM TO
KNOW WHERE HE'S DISAPPEARED TO.

24:57.713 --> 24:59.236
WE NEED TO
CATCH HIM SOON.

24:59.323 --> 25:01.108
WE CATCH SCOTT,

25:01.195 --> 25:03.110
WE MIGHT BE ABLE TO BRING
CARLISLE DOWN, AS WELL.

25:03.197 --> 25:04.546
I'LL KEEP MY EARS OPEN.

25:04.633 --> 25:06.766
YOU GOT SOMETHING MORE IMPORTANT
YOU'RE WORKING ON?

25:06.853 --> 25:10.073
NO. I'M SORRY, PETER.
I'M JUST DISTRACTED RIGHT NOW.

25:10.160 --> 25:11.771
I'm with Sara.AT HOME?

25:11.858 --> 25:13.424
Yeah.

25:13.512 --> 25:15.775
NEAL.

25:15.862 --> 25:17.167
YEAH?

25:17.254 --> 25:18.952
I like the two of you
together.

25:19.039 --> 25:20.301
She's a good influence
on you.

25:20.388 --> 25:21.781
YOU THINK SO?

25:21.868 --> 25:23.347
YEAH.

25:23.434 --> 25:25.349
DON'T BE A BAD INFLUENCE
ON HER.

25:25.436 --> 25:27.395
I'LL DO MY BEST.

25:27.482 --> 25:30.964
[ RECEIVER CLICKS ]

25:31.051 --> 25:32.400
FIGURE OUT A PLAN YET?

25:32.487 --> 25:35.229
I'M WORKING ON IT.

25:35.316 --> 25:37.579
LISTEN...

25:37.666 --> 25:39.755
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT TO BE
INVOLVED WITH THIS?

25:39.842 --> 25:42.410
WHATEVER WE END UP DOING,
IT PROBABLY WON'T BE LEGAL.

25:42.497 --> 25:45.369
ALL RIGHT, WHAT I DO
OCCASIONALLY FALLS IN
THE SAME GRAY AREA.

25:45.456 --> 25:46.762
THIS WON'T BE GRAY.

25:46.849 --> 25:49.939
I HAVE STRETCHED MORE LAWS
THAN I CARE TO ADMIT.

25:50.026 --> 25:52.202
THAT'S WHAT I LIKE
ABOUT YOU.
YEAH?

25:52.289 --> 25:55.771
I'M USUALLY RETURNING
THINGS TO THEIR RIGHTFUL
OWNER, THOUGH.

25:55.858 --> 25:57.860
WHAT?
THAT'S IT.

25:57.947 --> 25:58.992
YOU'RE A GENIUS.

25:59.079 --> 26:00.036
GUYS, I GOT AN IDEA.

26:05.215 --> 26:06.608
SHOW ME THE GLASS.

26:06.695 --> 26:09.306
HEY, WE GOT YOUR KEISTER
OFF THE HOOK.

26:09.393 --> 26:11.657
DON'T HOLD OUT
ON US NOW, KID.

26:13.789 --> 26:15.399
ARE YOU STILL SURE
ABOUT HIM?

26:15.486 --> 26:17.010
NOT SO MUCH.

26:17.097 --> 26:18.925
[ ZIPPER CLICKING ]

26:19.012 --> 26:20.187
[ THUD ]

26:23.451 --> 26:24.800
[ WHISTLES ]

26:24.887 --> 26:28.151
WOW, IT'S, UH...
BEAUTIFUL.

26:28.238 --> 26:29.588
LOOKS VERY COMFORTABLE.

26:31.198 --> 26:32.678
YOU CRACKED CARLISLE'S SAFE
TO GET THIS, RIGHT?

26:32.765 --> 26:34.244
YEAH.

26:34.331 --> 26:36.333
CAN YOU DO IT AGAIN?

26:36.420 --> 26:39.075
SAFE HAS
AN ELECTRONIC KEYPAD.

26:39.162 --> 26:41.251
MY BLACK BOX
DOES EVERYTHING.

26:41.338 --> 26:43.776
INCLUDING TAKING THE ART
OUT OF SAFE-CRACKING.

26:43.863 --> 26:46.213
THE ART WAS PROGRAMMING
THIS THING,

26:46.300 --> 26:48.694
WHICH I DID MYSELF.

26:48.781 --> 26:50.521
WE NEED TO GET YOU
INTO CARLISLE'S OFFICE

26:50.609 --> 26:51.958
SO YOU CAN
PUT THE BUSTIER BACK.

26:53.176 --> 26:55.048
THEN WE COULD
ANONYMOUSLY TIP PETER

26:55.135 --> 26:57.877
THAT THE DIAMONDS COULD BE FOUND
IN CARLISLE'S PRIVATE SAFE.

26:57.964 --> 26:59.052
PETER MOVES IN,
ARRESTS CARLISLE,

26:59.139 --> 27:00.967
WHO STOLE THE DIAMONDS
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

27:01.054 --> 27:02.272
IT WOULDN'T EVEN BE
PLANTING EVIDENCE.

27:02.359 --> 27:03.709
WE'D BE RETURNING IT.

27:03.796 --> 27:05.536
JUST LIKE YOU NEVER
STOLE THEM AT ALL.

27:05.624 --> 27:08.322
I'M NOT SURE THE SUIT
WILL SEE IT THAT WAY.

27:08.409 --> 27:10.585
NO. WE SHOULD NOT LET
PETER KNOW ABOUT THIS.

27:10.672 --> 27:12.587
THE PROBLEM IS, THEY'LL
HAVE AN EYE OUT FOR ANYONE
WHO LOOKS LIKE ME.

27:18.071 --> 27:20.943
HOW BIG IS THAT GRAY AREA
YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT?

27:26.122 --> 27:28.255
YOU STILL CHECKING
NEAL'S ANKLET?

27:28.342 --> 27:29.517
HE'S AT HOME.
BEEN THERE A WHILE.

27:29.604 --> 27:30.605
WHY DON'T YOU DROP BY?

27:30.692 --> 27:31.867
BECAUSE HE'S
UP TO SOMETHING.

27:31.954 --> 27:33.042
SOMETHING TO DO
WITH SCOTT?

27:33.129 --> 27:35.218
I THINK SO.
I'M GONNA LET IT PLAY OUT.

27:35.305 --> 27:36.655
YOU THINK
HE'LL LEAD YOU TO HIM.

27:36.742 --> 27:39.527
I HAVE A FEELING HE'S WORKING
ON SOME KIND OF PLAN.

27:39.614 --> 27:41.094
MAYBE MORE THAN ONE.

27:41.181 --> 27:44.358
COUPLE WEEKS AGO, A DEGAS
POPPED UP ON THE BLACK MARKET.

27:44.445 --> 27:45.881
ON THE LIST?

27:45.968 --> 27:47.970
NOT SURE. IT WAS PULLED
AFTER A COUPLE OF HOURS.

27:48.057 --> 27:49.668
NO DETAILS
BEYOND THE ARTIST.

27:49.755 --> 27:51.495
BUT HOW MANY NEW DEGASES
ARE THERE?

27:51.582 --> 27:53.497
[ DRAWER OPENS ]

27:58.067 --> 28:01.201
SHOWED UP THE SAME TIME
D.C. ART CRIMES CAME TO VISIT.

28:01.288 --> 28:03.072
PROBABLY COINCIDENCE.

28:03.159 --> 28:04.726
PROBABLY.

28:04.813 --> 28:07.381
I'M GONNA MOVE THIS --
TO BE SAFE.

28:13.517 --> 28:15.519
ALL RIGHT, WE NEED TO GET
INTO CARLISLE'S OFFICE,

28:15.606 --> 28:17.608
HACK THE SAFE,
AND RETURN THE BUSTIER.

28:17.696 --> 28:20.655
MOZZIE, YOU WILL KEEP AN EYE
ON CARLISLE.

28:20.742 --> 28:23.136
Mozzie:
I'LL KEEP ALL FOUR ON HIM.

28:26.530 --> 28:28.010
NOW, IT'S THE WEEKEND,

28:28.097 --> 28:29.838
SO THE ONLY PEOPLE IN
THE BUILDING WILL BE SECURITY.

28:29.925 --> 28:32.101
SECURITY WILL BE INCREASED
IN CARLISLE'S PENTHOUSE.

28:32.188 --> 28:33.973
LUCKILY, NOT
ON THE LOWER FLOORS.

28:34.060 --> 28:36.540
THE TELEPHONE-JUNCTION BOX
IS ON THE SECOND FLOOR.

28:36.627 --> 28:39.718
AND THAT IS WHERE
WE NEED TO GET SCOTT.

28:39.805 --> 28:41.632
DO I HAVE TO
BE THE BABY?

28:41.720 --> 28:44.287
MM-HMM.STANDARD RULE -- THE NEW MAN
ON THE TEAM IS THE BABY.

28:45.419 --> 28:47.247
THE ALARM SYSTEM WON'T BE --

28:47.334 --> 28:49.510
IT'S STATE-OF-THE-ART,
BUT GIVE ME A COUPLE HOURS.

28:49.597 --> 28:51.251
I CAN WRITE AN ALGORITHM THAT
CAN BYPASS THE SIGNAL TRAPS.

28:51.338 --> 28:53.035
THE ALARM SYSTEM
WON'T BE A PROBLEM.

28:53.122 --> 28:54.994
HOW'S THAT?BECAUSE WE'RE NOT
GONNA SET IT OFF.

28:55.081 --> 28:57.518
OUR OBSTACLES ARE A GUARD
AND A SECURITY DOOR

28:57.605 --> 28:59.520
THAT ONLY OPENS
FROM THE INSIDE.

28:59.607 --> 29:02.001
Mozzie: ALL THE WHILE, YOU JUST
HAVE TO AVOID THE CAMERAS.

29:17.407 --> 29:18.582
TO GET THROUGH
THE SECURITY DOOR,

29:18.669 --> 29:19.888
WE'LL NEED
MOZZIE'S AIR GUN.

29:19.975 --> 29:22.543
OH, BE WARNED --
LIKE AN OLSEN TWIN,

29:22.630 --> 29:24.763
THOUGH SHE SEEMS DEMURE,
SHE PACKS QUITE A PUNCH.

29:24.850 --> 29:26.242
[ METAL CLATTERS ]

29:47.394 --> 29:49.352
HEY, YOU CAN'T HAVE
THAT OPEN INDOORS.

29:49.439 --> 29:52.051
OH, I KNOW. IT'S BAD LUCK.
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO CLOSE IT.

29:52.138 --> 29:54.575
THE CATCH IS STUCK.
OUT.

29:54.662 --> 29:56.098
I'M SUPPOSED TO
MEET A FRIEND HERE.

29:56.185 --> 29:57.796
I DON'T CARE.
MEET HIM ON THE STREET.

29:57.883 --> 29:59.928
UH, DID YOU HEAR
SOMETHING EARLIER?

30:00.015 --> 30:02.061
I DID. YEAH.
THUNDER.

30:05.716 --> 30:07.196
ONCE SCOTT'S THROUGH
THE SECURITY DOOR,

30:07.283 --> 30:08.719
IT'S SARA'S TURN.

30:08.807 --> 30:10.721
Sara:
REALLY? A BARBIE?STANDARD RULE.

30:10.809 --> 30:12.245
THERE ARE NO
STANDARD RULES.

30:12.332 --> 30:14.290
I WOULD MUCH PREFER
TO BE THE SALT SHAKER.

30:14.377 --> 30:16.162
UH, CONSIDERING
YOUR ROLE IN THIS,

30:16.249 --> 30:17.641
THE BARBIE
IS MORE APROPOS.

30:20.166 --> 30:22.821
EXCUSE ME.
I'M HERE FOR MR. CARLISLE.

30:22.908 --> 30:24.474
I'M AFRAID
HE'S NOT IN.

30:24.561 --> 30:27.869
OH, I DON'T THINK
YOU UNDERSTAND.

30:27.956 --> 30:30.480
I'm here
forMr. Carlisle.

30:30.567 --> 30:33.875
I'LL HAVE TO [CLEARS THROAT]
CALL HIS OFFICE.

30:33.962 --> 30:36.225
MM. DO THAT.

30:36.312 --> 30:37.836
SCOTT SHOULD HAVE HACKED
INTO THE SWITCHBOARD BY THEN.

30:37.923 --> 30:39.272
SO, SCOTT -- HELLO.

30:39.359 --> 30:40.447
OH.COME ON. STAY WITH ME.

30:40.534 --> 30:41.796
YOU'LL BE
CARLISLE'S ASSISTANT.

30:41.883 --> 30:43.276
[ Ringing ]

30:43.363 --> 30:44.886
CARLISLE'S OFFICE.

30:44.973 --> 30:47.671
GUARD: Is Mr. Carlisle in?
There's a woman here who --

30:47.758 --> 30:49.891
ABOUT TIME!
HE'S BEEN WAITING FOR HER.

30:49.978 --> 30:52.720
SEND HER UP
IMMEDIATELY.

30:52.807 --> 30:53.939
HOW'S SHE LOOK?

30:56.767 --> 30:58.987
EXPENSIVE.

30:59.074 --> 31:00.684
SCOTT, YOU'LL PUT
THE SECURITY CAMERAS

31:00.771 --> 31:02.208
IN CARLISLE'S OFFICE
ON A LOOP,

31:02.295 --> 31:04.253
ESPECIALLY THE ONE YOU MISSED
THE FIRST TIME.

31:04.340 --> 31:07.082
ONCE SARA'S UP THERE,
SHE'LL LET YOU IN.

31:09.171 --> 31:10.912
EYES FRONT AND CENTER,
ROMEO.

31:10.999 --> 31:12.305
YES, MA'AM.

31:12.392 --> 31:14.350
DON'T CALL ME "MA'AM."

31:16.091 --> 31:17.876
THEN, SCOTT HACKS
THE SAFE'S KEYPAD AGAIN,

31:17.963 --> 31:20.182
PUTS THE BUSTIER BACK,
AND WE'RE HOME FREE.

31:28.190 --> 31:30.453
THIS IS NOT
THE SAME SAFE.

31:30.540 --> 31:31.846
YOU CAN'T CRACK THIS?

31:31.933 --> 31:33.935
OLD SCHOOL'S
NOT REALLY MY STYLE.

31:34.022 --> 31:36.807
OKAY, AND MINE IS NOT
CRACKING A SAFE IN MY BRA,

31:36.895 --> 31:39.158
BUT WE ADAPT.

31:51.822 --> 31:54.216
OUT FOR A STROLL?
TAKING IN THE SIGHTS?

31:54.303 --> 31:55.783
PETER --

31:55.870 --> 31:58.133
IMAGINE MY SURPRISE
WHEN I CHECKED YOUR ANKLET

31:58.220 --> 32:00.396
AND FOUND OUT THAT YOU WERE
RIGHT OUTSIDE CARLISLE'S OFFICE.

32:00.483 --> 32:02.921
I CAN EXPLAIN.
STARTING
WITH ROBIN HOODIE.

32:03.008 --> 32:04.226
IS HE IN THERE?

32:04.313 --> 32:06.489
I THINK IT'S BETTER
IF I DON'T ANSWER THAT.

32:06.576 --> 32:08.665
[ SIGHS ] BETTER FOR YOU
OR FOR ME?
FOR SCOTT.

32:08.752 --> 32:11.451
LOOK,
I'VE GOT A PLAN, OKAY?

32:11.538 --> 32:12.931
AND PART OF THAT PLAN
IS CONTINGENT

32:13.018 --> 32:14.367
ON YOU NOT KNOWING
WHAT IT IS.

32:14.454 --> 32:16.543
I'M NOT THE SHERIFF
OF NOTTINGHAM.

32:16.630 --> 32:18.632
DID I MISS
A CONVERSATION?

32:18.719 --> 32:20.068
I'M NOT THE BAD GUY.

32:20.155 --> 32:23.158
BUT SCOTT CAN'T BE ALLOWED
TO RUN AROUND LIKE THIS.

32:23.245 --> 32:25.682
HE'S GONNA GET SOMEBODY HURT,
STARTING WITH HIMSELF.

32:25.769 --> 32:27.206
I NEED TO BRING HIM IN.

32:27.293 --> 32:30.122
I KNOW.
GIVE ME AN HOUR.

32:30.209 --> 32:32.515
AFTER THAT, I THINK I CAN GET
HIM TO TURN HIMSELF IN TO YOU.

32:32.602 --> 32:34.517
YOU THINK?
I KNOW.

32:34.604 --> 32:36.911
[ CELL PHONE CHIMES ]

32:38.086 --> 32:39.870
LOOK, I HAVE TO GO.

32:39.958 --> 32:42.264
I'LL BE WAITING
RIGHT HERE.

32:42.351 --> 32:44.310
WHEN YOU COME BACK,
YOU BETTER HAVE HIM WITH YOU.

32:44.397 --> 32:46.007
THANK YOU.

32:46.094 --> 32:47.922
HI.

32:50.142 --> 32:51.970
RUNNING OUT OF UMBRELLAS.
WHAT'S WRONG?

32:52.057 --> 32:54.929
CARLISLE
UPDATED THE SAFE.

32:55.016 --> 32:56.452
IS HE SERIOUS?

32:56.539 --> 32:58.628
APPARENTLY.

32:58.715 --> 33:01.936
I INCREASED THE SENSITIVITY OF
THE MIKE ON THE PHONE 10 TIMES.

33:02.023 --> 33:03.764
YOU MADE A STETHOSCOPE
HAPPEN.

33:03.851 --> 33:06.114
I'M HITTING THE CYLINDERS.
IT'S NOT WORKING.

33:06.201 --> 33:09.030
THAT'S BECAUSE IT'S
A SIX-CYLINDER SAFE
WITH TWO FALSE GATES.

33:09.117 --> 33:11.032
FALSE GATES?YEAH, SAFE-CRACKING
BOOBY TRAPS.

33:11.119 --> 33:12.947
YOU HIT ONE, YOU HAVE TO
START ALL OVER AGAIN.

33:13.034 --> 33:14.731
MAY I?OF COURSE.

33:14.818 --> 33:16.820
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL GO BY TOUCH.

33:16.907 --> 33:19.214
YOU GO BY SOUND.

33:19.301 --> 33:21.086
YOU TWO MAKE
QUITE THE PAIR.

33:21.173 --> 33:22.913
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

33:23.001 --> 33:25.220
HELLO?

33:25.307 --> 33:27.483
ARE YOU DONE YET?

33:27.570 --> 33:31.618
UH, WE HIT A SNAG,
BUT WE'RE GONNA BE OUT SOON.

33:31.705 --> 33:33.446
OR NOT SO SOON.

33:33.533 --> 33:36.405
YEAH, WELL, UNSNAG
AS QUICKLY AS POSSIBLE.

33:36.492 --> 33:38.973
OKAY.
THANK YOU, MOZZIE.

33:41.193 --> 33:42.498
Both: WHAT IS IT?

33:42.585 --> 33:44.370
CARLISLE IS
ON HIS WAY HERE.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.113
ALL RIGHT, COME ON.

33:52.595 --> 33:54.858
THANKS, JONES.
I APPRECIATE THE BACKUP.

33:54.945 --> 33:57.165
NO NEED TO RUSH HERE.

33:57.252 --> 33:59.037
I'M NOT EXPECTING ANY...

34:01.039 --> 34:02.649
...TROUBLE.

34:02.736 --> 34:06.087
ON SECOND THOUGHT,
GO AHEAD AND RUSH.

34:06.174 --> 34:08.002
ALL RIGHT,
THAT'S THE THIRD GATE.

34:08.089 --> 34:09.699
ALL RIGHT, CARLISLE'S GOT TO
HAVE A SECURITY MONITOR

34:09.786 --> 34:11.832
AROUND HERE SOMEWHERE.

34:11.919 --> 34:13.834
THAT'S A GATE.
GOOD EAR.

34:13.921 --> 34:15.618
ARE YOU SAYING
YOU DIDN'T FEEL IT?

34:15.705 --> 34:17.751
I'M SAYING NICE EAR.

34:17.838 --> 34:20.667
HE IS DOWNSTAIRS.

34:20.754 --> 34:22.016
STILL TWO GATES TO GO.

34:22.103 --> 34:23.409
WE DON'T HAVE TIME.

34:23.496 --> 34:25.846
WAIT. PETER'S THERE.

34:25.933 --> 34:27.674
HE'S FLASHING HIS BADGE
AT CARLISLE.

34:27.761 --> 34:29.458
THE FED'S BUYING
US TIME? WHY?

34:29.545 --> 34:31.199
BECAUSE HE'S PETER.

34:31.286 --> 34:32.548
I HAVE A FEW
FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS

34:32.635 --> 34:33.723
FROM OUR MEETING
THE OTHER DAY.

34:33.810 --> 34:35.986
CAN IT WAIT?

34:36.074 --> 34:38.206
NO. IT CAN'T.

34:38.293 --> 34:40.687
OF COURSE.
COME, WE'LL GO INTO MY OFFICE.

34:40.774 --> 34:42.036
DOWN HERE IS FINE.

34:42.123 --> 34:44.473
BUT THE WHISKEY'S UPSTAIRS.
I INSIST.

34:44.560 --> 34:45.822
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

34:45.909 --> 34:47.781
AND I INSIST
RIGHT HERE IS FINE.

34:47.868 --> 34:50.131
AGENT BURKE, RIGHT?

34:50.218 --> 34:51.219
RIGHT.

34:51.306 --> 34:53.830
UNLESS
I'M UNDER ARREST,

34:53.917 --> 34:55.789
I'LL ANSWER YOUR QUESTIONS
IN MY OFFICE.

34:58.835 --> 35:00.010
AFTER YOU.

35:00.098 --> 35:01.447
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:05.842 --> 35:07.148
STOP.
ALL RIGHT,
THAT'S IT.

35:07.235 --> 35:08.541
THAT SHOULD BE
THE LAST GATE.

35:08.628 --> 35:11.500
ALL RIGHT.
ELEVATOR COMING UP!

35:11.587 --> 35:14.112
WE ONLY HAVE TIME
TO TRY ONCE.

35:14.199 --> 35:16.070
IT'S YOUR GO, KID.

35:21.206 --> 35:22.381
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

35:27.516 --> 35:30.432
NOW, WHAT IS IT
YOU WANTED TO DISCUSS?

35:30.519 --> 35:34.828
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THAT DIAMOND HEIST.

35:34.915 --> 35:36.873
THOUGHT THIS WAS
ABOUT SOME KID

35:36.960 --> 35:38.745
RUNNING AROUND
ROBBING PEOPLE.

35:40.790 --> 35:42.096
IT WAS.

35:44.142 --> 35:47.188
BUT IT GOT ME TO THINKING
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY BE

35:47.275 --> 35:49.712
IN THIS MONSTER SAFE
OF YOURS.

35:49.799 --> 35:53.368
I GUESS
YOU'LL NEVER KNOW.

35:53.455 --> 35:54.891
YOU'RE RIGHT.

35:54.978 --> 35:56.371
BECAUSE IT'S UNCRACKABLE,
RIGHT?

35:56.458 --> 35:58.504
COMPLETELY.
MM.

36:06.076 --> 36:07.948
YOU MUST HAVE LEFT IT OPEN
BY ACCIDENT, THEN.

36:11.081 --> 36:12.735
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

36:12.822 --> 36:17.131
THOSE LOOK LIKE THE DIAMONDS
I WAS TALKING ABOUT.

36:17.218 --> 36:21.091
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST,
MR. CARLISLE.

36:21.179 --> 36:23.572
THOSE --
THOSE AREN'T MINE.

36:23.659 --> 36:26.923
OH, YOU'RE ALLEGING THAT A THIEF
BROKE INTO YOUR OFFICE

36:27.010 --> 36:28.838
TO CRACK
AN UNCRACKABLE SAFE

36:28.925 --> 36:32.625
TO GIVE YOU MILLIONS
OF DOLLARS IN DIAMONDS?

36:32.712 --> 36:35.018
HANDS IN THE AIR.

36:35.105 --> 36:37.151
ALL RIGHT.

36:37.238 --> 36:38.544
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

36:38.631 --> 36:40.981
UNH-UNH-UNH. I WOULDN'T
DO THAT IF I WERE YOU.

36:41.068 --> 36:43.853
SORRY I'M LATE.

36:43.940 --> 36:45.203
DAMN,
THAT'S A HELL OF A VIEW.

36:47.074 --> 36:49.685
OH. YOU'RE GONNA
MISS THIS ONE.

36:53.385 --> 36:55.387
I WOULD LIKE TO GO PUT ON
SOMETHING A LITTLE LESS BREEZY.

36:55.474 --> 36:57.563
YES.
GO TALK TO HIM.

36:57.650 --> 36:58.651
[ SMOOCHES ]

36:58.738 --> 37:01.349
THANK YOU.
YEAH.

37:01.436 --> 37:03.133
[ SIGHS ]

37:06.615 --> 37:08.008
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO NOW?

37:08.095 --> 37:09.662
OH, COME ON.

37:09.749 --> 37:11.925
YOU DIDN'T REALLY THINK I WAS
GONNA TURN MYSELF IN, DID YOU?

37:12.012 --> 37:14.232
I WAS HOPING YOU WOULD.

37:14.319 --> 37:16.364
WOULD YOU HAVE
WHEN YOU WERE MY AGE?

37:16.451 --> 37:18.453
NO, I WOULDN'T HAVE.[ CHUCKLES ]

37:18.540 --> 37:21.282
BUT THIS ISN'T ABOUT ME.

37:21.369 --> 37:23.589
IT'S ABOUT PETER BURKE.

37:23.676 --> 37:25.547
HE'S THE SMARTEST MAN
I'VE EVER KNOWN.

37:25.634 --> 37:27.854
HE CAUGHT ME,
AND HE WILL CATCH YOU.

37:27.941 --> 37:30.204
ONLY QUESTION
IS WHEN.

37:30.291 --> 37:31.727
NOBODY'S THAT GOOD.

37:31.814 --> 37:33.555
HE IS, SCOTT.

37:33.642 --> 37:37.429
IF YOU TURN YOURSELF IN NOW,
HE'LL MAKE YOU A DEAL.

37:37.516 --> 37:39.082
IT'S THE BEST DEAL
YOU'RE EVER GONNA GET.

37:40.823 --> 37:43.696
YOU KNOW WHAT?
KEEP RUNNING.

37:43.783 --> 37:46.133
ALWAYS LOOKING
OVER YOUR SHOULDER,

37:46.220 --> 37:49.789
NEVER SLOWING DOWN LONG ENOUGH
TO SHARE YOUR LIFE WITH ANYONE.

37:49.876 --> 37:52.574
BECAUSE YOU KNOW
THAT THE SECOND YOU DO,

37:52.661 --> 37:54.968
THAT IS WHEN
HE WILL CATCH YOU.

37:55.055 --> 37:56.578
LET ME HELP YOU,
SCOTT.

37:57.840 --> 37:59.494
[ DOOR OPENS ]

37:59.581 --> 38:01.279
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

38:05.848 --> 38:07.241
WHERE'S SCOTT?

38:20.080 --> 38:22.125
ANY SIGN OF SCOTT?

38:22.212 --> 38:24.737
NOTHING. HE'S GONE
COMPLETELY TO GROUND.

38:24.824 --> 38:27.087
I SCREWED UP.

38:27.174 --> 38:28.958
YES, YOU DID.

38:29.045 --> 38:33.136
BUT...YOU HELPED GET CARLISLE
OFF THE STREETS.

38:33.223 --> 38:34.529
THAT'S A GOOD WIN.

38:37.793 --> 38:39.708
I ACTUALLY THOUGHT
I WAS GETTING THROUGH TO HIM.

38:39.795 --> 38:41.362
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:41.449 --> 38:42.668
DISAPPOINTING,
ISN'T IT?

38:42.755 --> 38:44.147
MM.

38:44.234 --> 38:46.193
YOU THINK
THEY'RE LISTENING,

38:46.280 --> 38:49.327
AND THEN THEY GO OFF AND DO
THE OPPOSITE OF WHAT YOU SAY.

38:49.414 --> 38:51.981
NOW HE COULD BE
ANYWHERE.

38:52.068 --> 38:54.593
HE REALLY COULD.

38:57.247 --> 38:59.424
BUT HE'S NOT.

39:03.645 --> 39:06.344
HE SAID HE'D ONLY
TURN HIMSELF IN TO YOU.

39:06.431 --> 39:09.085
SO...

39:09.172 --> 39:10.913
THIS IS THE GUY
WHO CAUGHT YOU?

39:11.000 --> 39:13.351
BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
YEAH.

39:13.438 --> 39:16.484
GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

39:16.571 --> 39:19.095
YOU STILL HAVE
THE PIECES YOU STOLE?

39:19.182 --> 39:21.576
DEPENDS. WHICH PIECES
DO YOU KNOW ABOUT?

39:21.663 --> 39:24.753
OH. HMM.
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:24.840 --> 39:27.843
THE MORE YOU COOPERATE,
THE BETTER DEAL I CAN GET YOU.

39:27.930 --> 39:29.802
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
SERVE SOME TIME.

39:31.760 --> 39:33.240
I KNOW.

39:33.327 --> 39:34.763
CAN I, UM...

39:34.850 --> 39:36.461
YEAH.

39:39.464 --> 39:42.510
SO, WHAT MADE YOU
DECIDE TO COME IN?

39:42.597 --> 39:45.339
BECAUSE STEALING STUPID THINGS
FROM RICH PEOPLE

39:45.426 --> 39:47.167
WAS ALREADY
GETTING BORING.

39:48.995 --> 39:51.824
OR BECAUSE WHAT YOU SAID
GOT TO ME.

39:51.911 --> 39:53.652
WHICHEVER MAKES YOU
FEEL BETTER.

39:55.175 --> 39:56.176
THANKS FOR THE HELP.

39:57.177 --> 39:59.222
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:02.661 --> 40:03.792
ANYTIME.

40:03.879 --> 40:06.491
JONES, COULD YOU
CUFF HIM AGAIN?

40:08.536 --> 40:10.799
Jones: REAL CUTE.

40:10.886 --> 40:13.715
LET'S TRY IT AGAIN.

40:20.113 --> 40:23.072
GIVE HIM SOME TIME.

40:23.159 --> 40:25.597
PEOPLE DON'T CHANGE
OVERNIGHT.

40:25.684 --> 40:27.773
BELIEVE ME, I KNOW.

40:27.860 --> 40:30.863
I WORK WITH LIVING PROOF
OF IT.

40:32.778 --> 40:35.345
BUT THEY DOCHANGE.

40:38.348 --> 40:40.263
YOU'RE NOT THE SHERIFF
OF NOTTINGHAM.

40:40.350 --> 40:41.917
I KNOW.

40:42.004 --> 40:44.485
I'M THINKING MORE
KING RICHARD THE LIONHEART.

40:44.572 --> 40:46.356
I'LL GO WITH THAT.GOOD.

40:57.977 --> 41:00.893
VICTOR MOREAU.

41:00.980 --> 41:03.461
VIC.

41:03.548 --> 41:05.463
VIC MOREAU.

41:09.597 --> 41:11.991
MOREAU.
VICTOR MOREAU.

41:12.078 --> 41:13.862
NICE TO MEET YOU.

41:13.949 --> 41:16.691
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

41:16.778 --> 41:18.476
JUST A SECOND.

41:22.958 --> 41:24.612
SURPRISED?

41:24.699 --> 41:26.135
HAPPILY.

41:26.222 --> 41:28.268
IT LOOKS LIKE I CAUGHT YOU
MID-SOMETHING.

41:28.355 --> 41:30.444
I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO TAKE A SHOWER.

41:30.531 --> 41:31.793
OH.

41:31.880 --> 41:34.448
IS THAT A STATEMENT
OR AN INVITATION?

41:38.060 --> 41:40.367
YES. YES.

41:40.454 --> 41:42.761
I'LL MEET YOU IN A SEC.ALL RIGHT.

41:49.158 --> 41:51.073
[ HANDLES SQUEAK ]
